
[1]munificence

   MUNIF'ICENCE, n. [L. munificentia; munus, a gift or favor, and facio,
   to make.]

   1. A giving or bestowing liberally; bounty; liberality. To constitute
   munificence, the act of conferring must be free, and proceed from
   generous motives.

   A state of poverty obscures all the virtues of liberality and
   munificence.

   2. In Spenser, fortification or strength. [L.munio, to fortify.] [Not
   used.]
